Time for action – configuring Eclipse to run a particular TestNG XML file
Perform the following steps to configure Eclipse to run a particular TestNG XML file:

On the top-bar menu of Eclipse, go to Run | Run Configurations.
Select TestNG from the set of configurations and click on the New Launch Configuration icon.
Time for action – configuring Eclipse to run a particular TestNG XML file
On the configuration window give a name My Test to the configuration.
Go to the Project section, click on Browse and select your project on the project window.
Now go to the Suite section and click on Browse. Select the mytestng.xml configuration.
Click on Apply, and then click on Run. This will run the selected testng XML configuration file. ...
